Tools

Communication

    1. [https://appear.in/]Appear.in - Browser-based, plugin-less group
       video calls.
    2. [https://bluejeans.com/]Bluejeans video conferencing app, great for
       large groups & live streams
    3. [https://codeshare.io/]Codeshare.io - Browser-based multi-user live
       code sharing with optional video chat.
    4. [https://fleep.io/]Fleep - Internal chat and collaboration tool for
       development teams
    5. [https://floobits.com/]Floobits - Remote pair programming with
       screen share. Integrates with Sublime, IntelliJ, Atom and others
    6. [https://www.flowdock.com/]Flowdock - Browser-based group chat for
       teams. Integrates with GitHub, Jira, Jenkins etc.
    7. [http://www.google.com/+/learnmore/hangouts/]Hangouts - Chat
       system, share desktop and video calls.
    8. [https://www.hipchat.com/]Hipchat - Great internal chat for
       hackers.
    9. [https://www.irccloud.com/]IRCCloud - Browser-based IRC client with
       permanent storage.
   10. [https://wiki.mumble.info/]Mumble Mumble is an open source voice
       chat software
   11. [https://precursorapp.com/]Precursor - Simple prototyping &
       brainstorming web app with real-time collaboration.
   12. [https://www.pukkateam.com/]PukkaTeam - Real team presence through
       regular automated selfies and one-click video calling
   13. [https://rocket.chat/]Rocket.Chat -- The Ultimate Open Source
       WebChat Platform.
   14. [https://screenhero.com/]ScreenHero - Real-time, HD screen sharing
       for collaboration in teams.
   15. [https://signal.org/]Signal - Encrypted, secure chat and video
       calls.
   16. [https://www.skype.com/]Skype - Video calls.
   17. [https://slack.com/]Slack - Chat system with loads of integration
       options.
   18. [https://talky.io/]Talky -- Truly simple video chat and screen
       sharing for groups
   19. [https://zoom.us/]Zoom -- High-quality group video and sharing
       screen, run on linux, record session and support telephone calls.

Project Management

    1. [https://asana.com/]Asana - Project management good for distributed
       teams.
    2. [https://www.getharvest.com/]Harvest - Time tracking
    3. [https://hitask.com/]Hitask - Easy task and project management for
       teams.
    4. [https://pinitto.me/]Pinitto.me - Lightweight realtime infinite
       virtual corkboard application (open source).
    5. [https://taskade.com/]Taskade - Real-time collaborative notes,
       checklists and outlines for teams.
    6. [https://trello.com/]Trello - Lean project boards.

Others

    1. [https://coffitivity.com/]Coffitivity - Coffitivity recreates the
       ambient sounds of a cafe to boost your creativity and help you work
       better.
    2. [https://funretro.github.io/distributed]Funretro - Funretro is a
       retrospective online board for distributed teams.
    3. [http://listen.hatnote.com/]Listen to Wikipedia (Hatnote) - Listen
       to the sound of Wikipedia's recent changes feed.
    4. [https://www.noisli.com/]Noisli - Noisli has a list of diferent
       ambient sounds that can be combined to boost creativity and focus.
    5. [https://qotoqot.com/qbserve/]Qbserve - Time tracking automation:
       freelance project tracking, timesheets, invoicing & real-time
       productivity feedback (Mac).
    6. [https://sundial.teleport.org/]Teleport Sundial - Manage the
       locations and timezones of your distributed team.
    7. [https://timingapp.com/]Timing - Automatic time and productivity
       tracking for Mac. Helps you stay on track with your work
       (especially important when working remotely). Also ensures that no
       billable hours get lost if you are billing hourly (Mac).

